financing, at a time when the country is desperate to improve its trade
imbalance? As a formerly redundant banker, I will testify for the great
numbers of bilingual, marketing-experienced bankers who would leap at the
opportunity to provide their services part time within a DTI-sponsored
scheme.
This could be structured specifically to help small businesses coping with
trade financing and other difficulties. R C Mitchell-Hegge,
