<HEADLINE>
FT  22 FEB 93 / International Company News: Sherwood Computer in two deals
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Sherwood Computer Services has paid Pounds 300,000 in cash to acquire THS
(Guernsey), in a move which strengthens its position in the insurance
companies market.
THS (Guernsey) comprises the majority of the assets and business of the
company which traded as THS Limited, a subsidiary of English &amp; American
Group. At the date of acquisition, THS (Guernsey) had net assets of Pounds
1.1m. The deal will give Sherwood the rights to a number of proprietary IBM
software products.
In a separate move, Sherwood announced a joint venture with Beta Computers
(Europe) to form a new company, Sherwood International. The company is 51
per cent owned by Sherwood, which acquired its equity by way of a
subscription for shares for Pounds 255,000 cash. The new company has been
formed to acquire the rights to PALACE, an advanced life and pensions
administration system with international potential.
</TEXT>
