FT  22 FEB 93 / Observer: Without tears
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Kingfisher and Darty, which last week agreed terms of their marriage, still
have a lot to work out between them. But Darty's finance director Gerard
Basini is clear about one thing. If Darty applies UK accounting principles
to its figures its profits look higher than under French rules. So while
Darty's numbers will be prepared on a UK basis for Kingfisher's benefit, he
says, 'we will use French rules for the taxman'.
